Product description

Length:14 Gauge 2 Conductor  |  Color:White

Designed to handle the rigors of outdoor installations, this 500 ft, budget-saving cable, is perfect for outdoor speakers, low voltage lighting and other outdoor or direct burial applications. CL3 rated for underground or in-wall use, the cable features a specially formulated white polyethylene jacket that is U/V resistant and provides protection against water damage. We manufacture to the highest standards with 41 strands of 99.9% pure copper conductors.

Specifications

  • Weatherproof Design
  • Double Insulated Cable
  • Continuous working temperature range: -20°C - 75°C
  • Voltage rating: 300V rams
  • Resistant to solvents chemicals gasoline and radiations
  • Resistant to UV
  • Direct Burial
  • RoHS complied
  • 41 strands
  • 14 gauge 2 conductor wire
  • 500ft Length
  • CL3R Rated for Residential and Commercial Use

How are ratings calculated?
To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzes reviews to verify trustworthiness.

M D W
5.0 out of 5 stars 750ft wired around pool
Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2018
Length: 12 Gauge 2 ConductorColor: WhiteVerified Purchase
2 spools purchased for a total of 1000ft. Aprox 700 ft used to connect the following set up— 1 TIC TFS50 Subwoofer, 2 TIC TFS25s omnidirectional speakers, and 4 TIC TFS10s to go around my pool and cover approximately 4000sq ft. of my backyard. They are driven by the Pyle PT8000CH amplifier and sourced by a Sonos Connect for Spotify and SiriusXM. The wire was flexible enough to be easily snaked through an interior wall, basement crawl space, 3/4” conduit to get outside and in a shallow trench (2 conduits needed because the 6 wires were too thick for one) . I directly wired each speaker to the amp, no “daisy chain”. The exterior sheath was thick enough to instill confidence that this will stand the test of time and the spooled box made it super easy to deploy the wire. Now to the speakers: Do they sound as good as my niles rock speakers that I left at my old house when we moved (stupid move on my part), no. Do they sound really good for 1/3 the price...Yes! Aprox $750 for speakers, $320 amp, $350 Sonos =$1,500 for a kick-ass loud as hell outdoor system. I’ll take it. Audiophile I’m not, but I enjoy loud Classic Rock, Hard Rock, Metal which pushes the speakers- no regrets on this purchase. Apologies in advance to my neighbors....I told my wife “if they complain, I won’t hear them over the music

5.0 out of 5 stars Very high quality cable, excellent price-point
Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2018
Length: 14 Gauge 2 ConductorColor: BlackVerified Purchase
I have used many different types of cable over the past six years, and I will say this is some of the higher quality cables I have come across. You can just as easily spend 30% less of other brands, and it would be just as sufficient, but so far I have had good luck with this. You can also just as easily purchase some GLS for double the price, and that would be some of the best quality cable you can get, but if you are budget minded, this will be more than sufficient. In the future, I would have no problem quoting this cable in future jobs.
